Legal_Issue: Whether the Board erred in dismissing the refugee claim based on alleged persecution due to HIV-positive status and gender
Governing_Law: Immigration and Refugee Protection Act (IRPA) sections 96 and 97
Evidence_Type: Claimed fear of persecution based on HIV status and gender
Basis_of_Claim: Persecution due to HIV-positive status and gender
Key_Factor_in_Determination: Insufficient evidence of serious discrimination or persecution
Application_Error: Alleged failure to adequately consider intersectionality and Gender Guidelines
Assessment_Standard: Adequacy of reasons, application of Gender Guidelines, consideration of intersectionality
Application_Factor: Intersectionality of gender and HIV status
Authority: Immigration and Refugee Board of Canada
Decision_Review_Issue: Adequacy of reasons and proper application of legal framework
Cause_of_Refusal: Lack of sufficient evidence of persecution or serious harm
Evidentiary_Issues: Insufficient evidence to support claim of persecution
Legal_Defense_or_Challenge: Challenge to adequacy of Board's reasoning and application of Gender Guidelines
Omission_Type: Alleged omission in considering intersectional discrimination
